# SkyWeb Change Log

Detailed implementation history for SkyWeb Analytics. The README keeps the current architecture, commands, and roadmap readable; this file carries the running phase log.

## Phase 8 — Macro Alerts

- Phase 8.1: Alert rule foundation, condition creation, and manual evaluation.
- Phase 8.2: Alert detail page and evaluation history.
- Phase 8.3: Scheduled alert evaluation visibility from the SkyServer worker.
- Phase 8.4: Triggered notification queue with acknowledge/dismiss behavior.
- Phase 8.5: Global Signals pill, dashboard alert card, Macro Overview signal strip, lifecycle wording, and severity styling.
- Phase 8.6: Alert preferences and delivery-prep contract.
- Phase 8.7: Dedicated Signal Center.
- Phase 8.8: Alert-rule search/filter/sort, inline edit, clone, remove confirmation, validation, and detail-page edit handoff.

## DN-0 to DN-2 — .NET Foundation

- Preserved the pre-.NET baseline.
- Added parallel `apps/web-dotnet` structure with `SkyWeb.Api` and `SkyWeb.Client`.
- Added API health, DB health, Swagger, CORS, Dapper/Npgsql, and PostgreSQL connection wiring.

## DN-3 — .NET Client Wiring + Proxy Bridge

- Wired the copied `.NET` lane React client to `SkyWeb.Api`.
- Added temporary proxy fallback so `SkyWeb.Client -> SkyWeb.Api -> SkyServer` could run while route families migrate.
- Moved the .NET-lane client to port `5175` so it can run beside the existing SkyWeb app on `5174`.

## DN-4 — Native Public Macro API

- Replaced `/api/public/macro/*` proxy behavior with native ASP.NET Core/C# endpoints.
- Kept `/api/auth/*` and `/api/skyweb/*` on proxy fallback at this stage.

## DN-5 — Native Auth API

- Replaced `/api/auth/*` proxy behavior with native ASP.NET Core/C# authentication endpoints.
- Mirrored opaque bearer-token behavior using SHA-256 token hashes in `auth.sessions`.
- Read user permissions from `auth.vw_user_permissions`.
- Preserved SkyWeb `appCode: SKYWEB` membership behavior.
- Left `/api/skyweb/*` on proxy fallback until DN-6 through DN-8.

## DN-5.1 — Public Macro Series Stabilization

- Began hardening native public macro reads for dashboard mini-chart usage.
- Preserved the public macro response contract while investigating indicator-series 500s.

## DN-5.2 — Indicator Series Regclass Fix

- Fixed PostgreSQL `to_regclass(...)` materialization by casting the result to `text` before reading it through Dapper/Npgsql.
- Scrubbed numeric `NaN` indicator-series values to `null` by casting through text before returning JSON.
- Targeted endpoints: `/api/public/macro/indicators/{indicatorCode}/series`.
